This paper deals with the problem of traffic classification in network security, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a novel method for distinguishing between encrypted and compressed packets, which involves evaluating the randomness of data streams. This method involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of sampling algorithms to alleviate scalability issues, which is a topic in network infrastructure (cs.NI). The evaluation of the proposed method involves the use of statistical analysis, which is a topic in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a new dataset for use in future research, which is a topic in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
